classes.name: Vector
classes.desc: An ordered collection where values are keyed using integers 0 thru n-1 in order.

funcs.name: __construct
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector built from the values produced by the specified Iterable.

funcs.name: isEmpty
funcs.desc: Returns true if the Vector is empty, false otherwise.

funcs.name: count
funcs.desc: Returns the number of values in the Vector.

funcs.name: items
funcs.desc: Returns an Iterable that produces the values from this Vector.

funcs.name: keys
funcs.desc: Returns an Iterable that produces the keys from this Vector.

funcs.name: lazy
funcs.desc: Returns a lazy iterable view of this Vector.

funcs.name: view
funcs.desc: Returns a lazy iterable view of this Vector.

funcs.name: kvzip
funcs.desc: Returns an Iterable that produces the key/value pairs from this Vector.

funcs.name: at
funcs.desc: Returns the value at the specified key. If the key is not present, an exception is thrown.

funcs.name: get
funcs.desc: Returns the value at the specified key. If the key is not present, null is returned.

funcs.name: set
funcs.desc: Stores a value into the Vector with the specified key, overwriting any previous value that was associated with the key; if the key is outside the bounds of the Vector, an exception is thrown.

funcs.name: setAll
funcs.desc: Stores each value produced by the specified KeyedIterable into the Vector using its corresponding key, overwriting any previous value that was associated with that key; if the key is outside the bounds of the Vector, an exception is thrown.

funcs.name: put
funcs.desc: Stores a value into the Vector with the specified key, overwriting any previous value that was associated with the key. If the key is outside the bounds of the Vector, an exception is thrown.

funcs.name: clear
funcs.desc: Removes all values from the Vector.

funcs.name: contains
funcs.desc: Returns true if the specified key is present in the Vector, returns false otherwise.

funcs.name: containsKey
funcs.desc: Returns true if the specified key is present in the Vector, returns false otherwise.

funcs.name: removeKey
funcs.desc: Removes the element with the specified key from this Vector and renumbers the keys of all subsequent elements.

funcs.name: add
funcs.desc: Adds the specified value to the end of this Vector using the next available integer key.

funcs.name: addAll
funcs.desc: Adds the values produced by the specified Iterable to the end of this Vector using the next available integer keys.

funcs.name: toArray
funcs.desc: Returns an array built from the values from this Vector.

funcs.name: getIterator
funcs.desc: Returns an iterator that points to beginning of this Vector.

funcs.name: map
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector of the values produced by applying the specified callback on each value from this Vector.

funcs.name: mapWithKey
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector of the values produced by applying the specified callback on each key and value from this Vector.

funcs.name: filter
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector of all the values from this Vector for which the specified callback returns true.

funcs.name: filterWithKey
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector of all the values from this Vector for which the specified callback returns true.

funcs.name: zip
funcs.desc: Returns a KeyedIterable produced by combined the specified Iterables pair-wise.

funcs.name: sort
funcs.desc: Uses the specified Collator to sort the Vector in place.

funcs.name: reverse
funcs.desc: Reverses the values of the Vector in place.

funcs.name: splice
funcs.desc: Splices the values of the Vector in place (see the documentation for array_splice() on php.net for more details.

funcs.name: linearSearch
funcs.desc: Returns index of the specified value if it is present, -1 otherwise.

funcs.name: shuffle
funcs.desc: Shuffles the values of the Vector randomly in place.

funcs.name: fromItems
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector built from the values produced by the specified Iterable.

funcs.name: fromArray
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector built from the values from the specified array.

funcs.name: slice
funcs.desc: Returns a Vector built from the specified slice of values from the specified Vector.
